Vegetarian "Meatloaf"

Loaf:
4 tbsp (60mL) olive oil
3 stalks celery, diced
1 medium yellow onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, diced
salt and pepper to taste
2 c (480mL) ground nuts and seeds of choice
1 1/2 c (360mL) cooked brown rice
1/2 c (120mL) nutritional yeast
3 eggs, beaten
1 tbsp (15mL) tamari or shoyu

Preheat oven to 350F. Copok the rice per package directions. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat. Saute the celery and onion until soft and translucent. Add garlic and saute another minute; season with salt and pepper to taste. In a food processor, grind nuts and seeds to a coarse texture, being careful not to make nut butter. Place remaining ingredients, including 3 tbsp oil, into processor and pulse to combine. Spread into greased loaf pan and cook for 35 min.

Sauce:
1/2 c (120mL) ketchup
1 tbsp (15mL) tomato paste
3 tbsp (45mL) worcestershire sauce
1/2 c (120mL) maple syrup
1/2 tsp (7.5mL) salt
1/2 tsp (2.5mL) chili powder
1/2 tbsp (7.5mL) dijon mustard
1/4 tsp (1.25mL) black pepper

Combine all ingredients in a bowl and whisk.

After first 35 min of baking, pull loaf out and cover with sauce. Return to oven and continue cooking for 5-8 min or until the sauce has thickened.

Leftovers can be stored in airtight container in refrigerator for up to 1 week. Reheat in the oven or on a skillet.

Nutrition:
Serves 8
calories: 382
total fat: 18g
saturated fat: 3g
monounsaturated fat: 8g
cholesterol: 70mg
sodium: 335mg
carbs: 40g
dietary fiber: 10g
sugar: 17g
protein: 18g
